Prodigal Son<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The night air grew colder as he pressed on...The cold chill of the wind bit into his skin...This night was not unlike the others he had spent in these wretched mountains ... searching... His honor had been tested and yes it had been some time ... Completion of this task was vital ... Reach the Summit ... Claim his prize and return to his beloved sanctuary ... The Dark forest he envisioned in the back of his mind ... Too long had he struggled to gain understanding of his ways ... Too long had he neglected the one thing that made him feel whole ... His Family ... The Violent Harvest ... His journey of enlightenment had brought him to lands far away ... With out so much as a good bye he left them all ... He knows not if they noticed his passing for the time was ideal ... The uprising of Innoruuks children was at hand ... His heart longed to be at the side of his comrades ... Shedding blood ... Drinking from the very skulls of his enemies ... With all this in mind the young Shadow Knight plunged headlong into the darkness ... Still searching for his elusive prey ... He must return to Neriak soon ... Soon or he could perish in this frozen wasteland...<br>
<br>
Darkehn climbed to the very top of the world in search of his prize ... With only his meager cloth pants and tunic as protection ... A sudden gust of wind brought him to his knees ... The snow had begun to turn to frozen rain some time ago and was beginning to cut his flesh ... Through the haze of frost he spied his goal ... perched ...u..p...o..n... Then it all went black .... He had succomed to the elements ... Surely he would die he thought as his vision blurred and his strength wained ... He fell to his side and sank into a snow drift ... he was quickly covered by the icey deposits ... Not how he thought he would die ... Not by any stretch of the imagination ... Battle was where he was supposed to die ... Slaughtering the Lightborn at the Frost Gate ... He had witnessed it in his very dreams ... The cold quickly numbed his extremeties and soon even his brain ... With his last breathes he muttered a prayer to Innoruuk ...<br>
Warmth spread around him .... He wakes in a familiar but Unknown place ... He is lying in front of a warm fire wrapped in Bear skins ... His vision is still blurred but he can barely make out the face looking down upon him...<br>
<br>
&quot;Selilya?&quot; he can barely issue forth the name .... Then Darkness takes him again... <br>
