Re: Prodigal Son<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;He's stirring again,&quot; Lenaesha informed the monk. &quot;Poor creature...he just keeps muttering that name. She must be someone very important to him.&quot; Lanashae pulled the bear skins back over Darkehn's prone form and stroked his silver hair much as she would have done for a sick child.<br>
<br>
Lynxe pulled the stool next to the makeshift bed and sat down heavily. He was weary now but glad he had found Darkehn before it was too late. He'd achieved his prize...and Lynxe would not let him be cheated of the victory. Lynxe knew it was time for Darkehn to return to his people. There wasn't much more this monk could teach him... He knew that sometimes, life is a far better instructor.<br>
<br>
Lynxe looked over at his hostess. Lenaesha was married to Prumathon Jaxallion. It was quite mind-boggling to find their cabin out here in the frozen northern wastelands. What he found even more remarkable was that she was a dark elf, like Darkehn, and he was a barbarian. Lynxe just shook his head. He was not one given to understand the secrets of love between two people. He'd not had time for such nonsense. He knew that Darkehn had mistaken her for Selilya. In his current physical state, he could have just as easily confused the barbarian for his...his what?<br>
<br>
After Darkehn had come to train with him, Selilya had come looking for him. No wonder Darkehn was so taken...Lynxe had to admit, she seemed to have some magic about her. There was something else Lynxe noticed, however, and he couldn't quite put his finger on it at their first encounter. She had been fiercely protective of Darkehn, and he knew that she would have dispatched him right then and there if he couldn't convince her of his intentions for his new pupil. They continued a conversation for hours...until the night air chilled the both of them. She had headed on to the Frontier Mountain fortress, and Lynxe watched her vanish into the trees before he headed back to the tent that he shared with Darkehn.<br>
<br>
&quot;You'll be better soon, friend,&quot; he whispered to Darkehn. The months had flown by for them he mused. Darkehn had been quite stubborn at first. It cost his quite a few bumps and bruises. He had lacked real discipline. His way back then was to attempt to &quot;brute force&quot; his way through every situation. Yet, Lynxe, the Monk, had persisted...and had been very patient. These last few weeks had seen a changed Shadow Knight emerge... The final step...ascending the highest peak in the frozen land...was all that kept him from passing on to the ranks of &quot;graduate.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, Darkehn, had become his favorite pupil, and perhaps even worthy of learning many of the secrets Lynxe held close. So, when the day came to conquer the last phase, he sighed. Darkehn had seemed to be battling a slight case of sniffles, but that was common in the higher plateaus. Yet, Lynxe, decided to keep an eye on his prized pupil's progress. When Darkehn had laid his fingers around the handle of the covered box, he collapsed...and Lynxe watched and waited for<br>
him to get up...to yell &quot;Victory is Mine&quot;...but there was no movement.<br>
<br>
Lynxe had been most fortunate in stumbling into the barbarian. Prumathon didn't hesitate at all when he saw the two rather &quot;frozen&quot; individuals stumbling down the face of the peak. He scooped Darkehn up from the shoulders of the<br>
monk and within a brief lapse of time, they had made their way to the barbarian's cottage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Prumathon?&quot; the monk began. &quot;I must get word to his friends. It is time for this young one to go home...to his destiny. I leave him here in your capable care. Your kindness to the both of us has been....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Shhh,&quot; Lanaesha raised her hand to silence him. &quot;It is our pleasure to help. It's been so long since I have seen one from my homeland. Go...go...he will be just fine here until you return.&quot;<br>
<br>
Lynxe patted his pupil on the head once more...picked up his traveling pack...and headed out the door to secure Darkehn's future.<br>
