<br>
It did seem that the night air had chilled just slightly upon his leaving the young Shadow Knight to recuperate under the care of the the strange couple. Lynxe pushed forward into the darkness made even darker by the absence of moonlight. The last few months had been quite an eye opener for the monk. He learned just as much from Darkehn as the dark elf learned from him. The brash youth did indeed have a certain quality about him. He wondered why Selilya cared so much for his well being. Maybe his student did indeed have a destiny greater than just a valaint warrior. Could his return to his people spark some unknown flame? Lynxe pondered all of this as he jogged through the frozen land toward the Frost Gate. He had spent much time in these hills and mountains as he was born in the nearby city of Qeynos. This is where he built his extreme tolerance to the elements. He could easily withstand many a night at sub zero temperatures and not suffer from even the slightest cold. That is why he sent Darkehn here. He knew that this would test the very core of darkehns being. Lynxe only wished he had given the young Shadow Knight more time. But lifes lessons are only learned through experience. Lynxes strove onward in search of Darkehns self procclaimed guardian. Selilya...That name haunted him. She was indeed a sight to behold. Power and grace neatly wrapped into the slight frame of a beautiful dark elf female. He had met with her a few times in the past. They had even shared a lengthy conversation around a small camp fire in the Over There. Her thoughts were hard to read but years of study had made Lynxe a very capable empath. He knew the ways of the Dark Elf more now than before, but even then he could see here selfless devotion to her cause. <br>
<br>
Lynxe only had one goal now....To find her. he had recieved word of a blood bath ensuing in the Eastern Common Lands. He would start his search there. The blood and carnage would surely bring forth the Mistress of the Dead. This he was sure of...  <br>
